Anchor University has said its public lecture scheduled to hold on Thursday (today) will seek to connect gown to town through the contribution of intellectual resources to national development. The convener of the lecture, Prof Tunde Ope-Davies, disclosed this in a statement on Wednesday, adding that the Speaker of the Lagos State House of Assembly, Mudashiru Obasa, will chair the event. He said, “The first ‘Distinguished Public Lecture’ of the Faculty of Humanities which will be held at Anchor University, Ayobo, is a serious academic tradition designed to contribute our intellectual resources to public debates and national development. “We seek to connect ‘gown with town,’ establish deeper relationship with our community and enhance the relevance of our university to the larger society.” Ope-Davies added that the lecture will be chaired by dignitaries, including the Pro-Chancellor of AU, Pastor William Kumuyi. “The lecture will be chaired by the Speaker, Lagos State House of Assembly Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa; the Pro-Chancellor of Chrisland University, Ogun State, Prof Ayodeji Olukoju; the Chairman, Lagos State Security Trust Fund, Dr Ayo Ogunsan; the Vice-Chancellor of AU, Prof Joseph Afolayan, and the proprietor of AU, Pastor (Dr) William Kumuyi,” he added. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com